narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learned how to think about bonds/structured products/options/etc. in some contexts. Good background if you care about these things.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It's a good course. Lecture is a little dry (reading the lecture notes works), and average engagement was pretty low. The cases were OK but we were fairly unmotivated to produce good work, and grading was kind of inconsistent.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: It's fine, and I actually learned a lot of interesting stuff. I took it Cr/D, and I'm not sure I would recommend taking it for a grade unless you and a few of your friends are motivated to work on the cases together.
